name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-ExtraCondensedThin', Everything looks good.

MS NID 16/17

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtraCondensed Thin' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtCond Thin' (NID 1).

Noto Serif Myanmar ExtCond Light Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-ExtraCondensedLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtraCondensed Light' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtCond Light' (NID 1).

MS NID 6

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifMyanmar-ExtraCondensedMedium', Everything looks good.

Noto Serif Myanmar ExtCond Med Regular (NotoSerifMyanmar-ExtraCondensedMedium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtraCondensed Medium' ≠ 'Noto Serif Myanmar ExtCond Med' (NID 1).
